'''桂格·布萊登'''（{{lang-en|Gregg Braden}}，{{bd|1954年|6月28日||}}）是[[美國|美國]][[新紀元運動|新紀元]]作家。出生於[[密蘇里州|密蘇里州]]，早年曾當過太空電腦系統設計師、電腦地質師和技術操作經理。他花了多年時間研究如何將[[靈性|靈性]]和[[科學|科學]]結合<ref>{{Cite web|title=Gregg Braden: "La ciencia está secuestrada por las empresas, los políticos y las religiones"|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/vida/20150522/54431790127/entrevsita-gregg-braden-ciencia.html|accessdate=2021-01-14|date=2015-05-21|work=La Vanguardia|language=es|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129174053/https://www.lavanguardia.com/vida/20150522/54431790127/entrevsita-gregg-braden-ciencia.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Gregg Braden: "La mayor crisis a la que nos enfrentamos es la del pensamiento"|url=https://www.elmundo.es/vida-sana/mente/2017/05/11/5900c13b22601d126f8b45d0.html|accessdate=2021-01-14|date=2017-05-11|work=ELMUNDO|language=es|archive-date=2019-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808211222/https://www.elmundo.es/vida-sana/mente/2017/05/11/5900c13b22601d126f8b45d0.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

布萊登因聲稱[[地球|地球]]的磁極即將[[地磁逆轉|反轉]]而聞名<ref> {{cite book|last=Aveni|first=Anthony|year=2009|title=''The End of Time: The Maya Mystery of 2012''|publisher=University Press of Colorado|location=Boulder, Colorado|isbn=978-0-87081-961-2|url=https://archive.org/details/endoftimemayamys00aven}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Stray|first=Geoff|title=''Beyond 2012: Catastrophe Or Awakening?: A Complete Guide to End-of-Time Predictions''|url=https://archive.org/details/beyond2012catast0000stra|publisher=Inner Traditions / Bear & Co|year=2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Greer|first=John Michael|title=''Apocalypse Not: Everything You Know About 2012, Nostradamus and the Rapture Is Wrong''|url=https://archive.org/details/apocalypsenothis0000gree|publisher=Viva Editions<!-- [[Cleis_Press|Cleis Press]] -->|year=2011|isbn=978-1-93674-000-0}}</ref>。他認為[[地球磁場|地球磁場]]的變化可能會對人類[[DNA|DNA]]產生影響<ref>{{cite book|last=Peirce|first=Penney|title=''Frequency: The Power of Personal Vibration''|publisher=Simon & Schuster|year=2009}}</ref>。他還主張人類的情感會影響DNA、集體祈禱可能具有治癒效果<ref> {{cite book|last=Johnston|first=Laurance|title=''Alternative Medicine and Spinal Cord Injury''|publisher=Demos Medical Publishing|year=2006|p=145}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Douty|first=Linda|title=''How Can I See the Light When It's So Dark?: Journey to a Thankful Heart''|url=https://www.churchpublishing.org/products/howcaniseethelightwhenitssodark|publisher=Church Publishing, Inc.|year=2007|p=13|isbn=978-0-81922-257-2|access-date=2021-01-14|archive-date=2017-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218124629/https://www.churchpublishing.org/products/howcaniseethelightwhenitssodark|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2009年，其著作《Fractal Time》成為《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》[[紐約時報暢銷書榜|暢銷書]]<ref>{{Cite news|title=Hardcover Advice & Misc. Books - Best Sellers - Books - April 5, 2009|url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2009/04/05/hardcover-advice/|newspaper=The New York Times|accessdate=2021-01-14|language=en-US|author=|date=2009-04-05|archive-date=2019-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330093958/https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2009/04/05/hardcover-advice/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

